.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH bus 1  "bus " 
.SH NAME
bus \- Messaging bus: send · inbox (role@cave, via the cave inbox/outbox files)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbus\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Messaging bus: send · inbox (role@cave, via the cave inbox/outbox files)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
bus\-send(1)
Send a message to a role@cave address (appends to the cave outbox)
.TP
bus\-inbox(1)
Show inbox messages bound for this agent (advances the read cursor)
.TP
bus\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
